<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-16T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-16T12:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/12261: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-16T18:00:00+01:00">November 16, 1918—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 17—6:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2368. Learned that detachment of troops have [occupied?] Fiume, but some
                            doubt exists whether Italians only or international force.</p>
                        <p>The Fiume Italian Deputy, who called on me to-day, states that after talk
                            with Premier Orlando, he [sent?] a note to Baron Sonnino the evening the
                            latter left Rome for Paris requesting that Fiume be taken under the
                            Allies.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>